Alexander McLAREN, Petitioner, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent. No. 8771. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 16, 1938. Thomas N. Fowler, of Seattle, Wash., for petitioner. James W. Morris, Asst. U. S. Atty. Gen., and J. P. Wenchel, Chief Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for respondent, consented to by counsel for petitioner, ordered petition to review herein dismissed for failure of petitioner to file record ánd docket cause; that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
